==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clinker-built
<hw>Clink"er-built</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Having the side planks (of a boat) so arranged that the lower edge
of each overlaps the upper edge of the plank next below it like
clapboards on a house. See <er>Lapstreak</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinkstone</ent>⟦br⟧
